 the pipeline is working as intended with these mitigations in place.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":711,"cache_read_input_tokens":39060,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":711},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4665351-3d09-43da-b45f-67547abfbbfd","uuid":"2fa61230-5cee-4d66-be14-8b2777700e1d","request_id":"req_011CcMtP7FP2LZiGDyJjWjXs"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015BQE3NGpg8KXZgES1fzLXQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the information needed. Let me summarize the complete picture:\n\n**DIAGNOSIS: Root Cause**\n\nThe data skew report confirms:\n- `total_records=100,000`, `distinct_user_ids=1,000`\n- `hot_user_id=999` holds `50,000` records — **50% of all data**\n- `skew_ratio=500x` (far above the 10x threshold)\n\nWhen Stage 3 runs `GROUP BY user_id`, Spark shuffles all data for `user_id=999` into a single partition. With only 256MB of executor memory, that one massive partition triggers `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n**FIX: What was applied (etl-job.yaml:30-37)**\n\nThe YAML already contains the fix — a combination of Option B + Option C:\n\n```yaml\n--conf spark.executor.memory=1g                      # ↑ from 256m (4x increase)\n--conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true               # AQE on\n--conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true      # AQE splits hot partitions\n```\n\nAQE's skew join detection is the right long-term fix: it automatically splits the oversized `user_id=999` partition into sub-partitions at runtime, so no single executor is overwhelmed regardless of skew severity.\n\n**VERIFICATION**\n\n```\n$ kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\nNAME      STATUS     COMPLETIONS   DURATION   AGE\netl-job   Complete   1/1           87s        20m\n\n$ kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job --tail=3\n...\nPi is roughly 3.1418896628377935\nspark_etl_pipeline_verified       ← success sentinel confirmed\n```\n\nThe ETL job completed in 87s with `spark_etl_pipeline_verified` printed at the end. All three success criteria are met:\n\n| Criterion | Status |\n|---|---|\n| OOM identified in Stage 3 | Confirmed via diagnostic server + skew_info.txt |\n| Data skew diagnosed (user_id 999, 500x ratio) | Confirmed |\n| Fix applied (AQE + 1g memory) | Applied in etl-job.yaml |\n| ETL job completed successfully | `Complete` 1/1, `spark_etl_pipeline_verified` |"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":711,"cache_read_input_tokens":39060,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":711},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4665351-3d09-43da-b45f-67547abfbbfd","uuid":"5b91a76c-8450-4fdc-8ae3-31b519108a28","request_id":"req_011CcMtP7FP2LZiGDyJjWjXs"}
